{"name": "aind-qcportal-schema", "metadata": {"name": "aind-qcportal-schema", "version": "0.2.3", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["pydantic", "aind-data-schema"], "summary": "Generated from aind-library-template", "upload_time": 1731700645}, "documentation": ["# aind-qcportal-schema\n\nInstall with `pip install aind-qcportal-schema`\n\n## Usage\n\nThis package includes classes that are expected by the [QC Portal](https://github.com/AllenNeuralDynamics/aind-qc-portal) for generating custom `QCMetric` value views. For example you can generate dropdowns with specific options, multi-select (checkbox) values with options, etc... \n"], "modules": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.DropdownMetric", "bases": ["BaseModel"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.DropdownMetric.value", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.DropdownMetric.options", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.DropdownMetric.status", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Status", "xref": {"fqname": "aind_data_schema.core.quality_control.Status", "project": "aind-data-schema"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.DropdownMetric.type", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Dropdown metric schema\n\nThe value field should either be \"\" or one of the options\n\nRenders as: https://panel.holoviz.org/reference/widgets/Select.html", "HOW TO USE", "These objects should be attached to the QCMetric.value field. They affect how the", "metric is rendered in the QC portal. The value field should be set to the value of the metric!"]}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.CheckboxMetric", "bases": ["BaseModel"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.CheckboxMetric.value", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.CheckboxMetric.options", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.CheckboxMetric.status", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Status", "xref": {"fqname": "aind_data_schema.core.quality_control.Status", "project": "aind-data-schema"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.CheckboxMetric.type", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Checkbox metric schema\n\nThe value field should either be \"\" or one or more of the options as a list\n\nRenders as: https://panel.holoviz.org/reference/widgets/Checkbox.html"]}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.RulebasedMetric", "bases": ["BaseModel"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.RulebasedMetric.value", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.RulebasedMetric.rule", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Rulebased metric schema\n\nIn general you should not be using this schema! This is a special metric that allows for a rule\n to be evaluated by the QC portal and the status to be set based on the result. The situation\n where you use this is if the value needs to be set by a user and the rule is fairly simple, e.g.\n the user sets the value to the number of visible cells, and the rule is \"value>10\". \"value\" *must*\n be included in the rule statement!\n\nIf you are computing the status of an object yourself you should put the rule in the QCMetric.description field."]}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.MultiAssetMetric", "bases": ["BaseModel"], "methods": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.MultiAssetMetric.validate_type_if_options", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "v", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.MultiAssetMetric.values", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.MultiAssetMetric.options", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.metric_value.MultiAssetMetric.type", "type": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Multi-asset metric schema\n\nIn general you should not be using this schema! This is a special\nmetric that allows for a single metric to be evaluated across multiple assets.\n\nThis should be used in combination with the QCEvaluation.evaluated_assets field."]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "aind_qcportal_schema", "documentation": ["Init package"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "aind_qcportal_schema.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}]}